def removeEdge(n, edges, removeEdge):
    # modifying the edges to remove the specified edge
    new_edges = [e for e in edges if e != removeEdge]
    return findCriticalAndPseudoCriticalEdges(n, new_edges)
```
This function will return the new list of critical and pseudo-critical edges along with the new weight of the MST. 

This solution runs in O(E^2) time where E is the number of edges in the graph. There are more efficient algorithms to solve this problem such as using a Sparse Table for Range Minimum Queries to run in O(E log E) time.

