1. Sort the array using the `Arrays.sort()` method, which has a time complexity of O(n log n).
2. Use two pointers, `i` and `j`, to traverse the array.
3. Compare each element with the next element.
4. If they are not equal, move the element at index `i` to index `j` and increment `j`.
5. After traversing the array, add the last element to the array at index `j`.
6. Create a new array using `Arrays.copyOf()` method to copy the elements from index 0 to index `j`.
7. Print the result.

The time complexity of this solution is O(n log n) due to the sorting step.

